    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="159"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793B.56/3–150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 1, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192. It is noted from various Emb reports that <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> contemplates increase flow mil assistance Tibet. Inasmuch as
                    Commie-controlled Tibet wld represent threat Nepal and India, Dept interested
                    fullest available info exact nature this assistance.</p>
                <p>In ur discretion Dept wld appreciate your ascertaining informally through <gloss
                        target="#t_UKHC1">UKHC</gloss> fol: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Volume assistance <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> has already
                            given Tibet,</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Whether rate such assistance being increased,</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>What definite steps taken by <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> re
                            training Tibetan mil units,</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Brit attitude re mil assistance Tibet.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Dept also interested info concerning Tibetan plans resist commie incursion and
                    type of mil assistance Tibet required. What in ur opinion be probable <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> reaction suggestion US and/or UK collaboration
                    with India meeting these needs? <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Dept hopeful
                    India can meet justifiable Tibetan defense requirements and believes it highly
                    desirable India continue bear primary responsibility for doing so within its
                    capabilities, but shld it be unable do so Dept wld appreciate being so <pb
                        facs="0329" n="315" xml:id="pg_315"/> informed. In any event, conversations
                    with <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> this time wld appear premature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
